cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.GR

The paper deals with computational complexity analysis of various edge-matching puzzles, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The analysis involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) to solve the puzzles, as well as computational geometry (cs.CG) to analyze the triangular edge matching. Game theory (cs.GT) is also used to analyze the 2-player games. Finally, graph theory (cs.GR) is used to model the edge-matching puzzles as graphs and analyze their complexity.
